OBJECTIVE
• Extract only camera-visible facts (subject, action, setting).
• If the passage is non-visualizable (taste/odor/abstract chemistry/microscopic processes), choose a minimal, literal proxy scene (e.g., clear beaker of water on plain surface).

RULES (strict)
• No invented facts, metaphors, similes, mood words not in INPUT.
• Photography style cue required (“a photo of …”) to bias realism.
• Decide lens & focal by subject: portraits 24–35 mm; small objects/plants macro 60–105 mm; motion 100–400 mm; landscapes 10–24 mm.
• Camera position/proximity/lighting only if implied; else eye-level, neutral lighting.
• **Aspect ratio is always Square 1:1** (override any other choice).
• Negative prompts = plain items to omit (no “no/don’t”).
